OL,3,CEnergy bills to fall by #117 for
OL,4,Cmillions of British households from
OL,5,CApril
OL,7,FResponding to the energy price cap
OL,8,Fdrop, Prime Minister Sir Keir Starmer
OL,9,Fsaid: "Energy bills are at the front
OL,10,Fof everybody's mind, and I know
OL,11,Fthey've been too high for too long.
OL,13,F"I promised to bring bills down and I
OL,14,Fmeant it. And today - because of the
OL,15,Factions this government took at the
OL,16,Flast budget - the price cap on energy
OL,17,Fbills has come down by #117.
OL,26,@qD@GOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1772055663
OL,3,CEnergy bills to fall by #117 for
OL,4,Cmillions of British households from
OL,5,CApril
OL,7,F"That means lower energy bills for
OL,8,Fmillions across the country, but I
OL,9,Fknow there is more to do and my
OL,10,Fgovernment is pulling every lever to
OL,11,Fbear down on the cost of living and
OL,12,Fprotect the pound in the pockets of
OL,13,Fworking people."
OL,15,FChancellor Rachel Reeves said:
OL,16,F"Cutting the cost of living is this
OL,17,Fgovernment's number one priority and I
OL,18,Fknow energy bills are one of the
OL,19,Fbiggest concerns, that's why at the
OL,20,Fbudget I said we would bear down on
OL,21,Fenergy bills.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@PO]xD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
